26913	 * DSML in an order that is semantically valid but not byte-for-byte equal to the
26914	 * canonical prompt we will see on the next request.  Rewriting only the token
26915	 * checkpoint is not enough: the backend still contains raw and compressed rows
26916	 * for the old suffix.  Until we have a real frontier snapshot at the
26917	 * rewrite point, any replacement behind the live end reports that a rebuild is
26918	 * needed without mutating the session.  The server may still find an older disk KV
26919	 * checkpoint before falling back to a full replay. */
